<p>If you ever implemented comparison operators in C++, you know what a menial, tedious task it is. You have to define six operators (<code>==</code>, <code>!=</code>, <code>&lt;</code>, <code>&lt;=</code>, <code>&gt;</code>, <code>&gt;=</code>).</p>
<p>With C++20, you can simply <code>=default</code> the spaceship operator and it will generate all the six <code>constexpr</code> and <code>noexcept</code> operators for you and they perform lexicographical comparison.</p>
